b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15029.htm)  [Next](sbe15031.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 51\n\n### NINTH ANUV\xc3\x82KA 1.\n\n1\\. (What is necessary?) The night, and learning and practising the Veda. The\ntrue, and learning and practising the Veda. Penance, and learning and\npractising the Veda. Restraint, and learning and practising the Veda.\nTranquillity, and learning and practising the Veda. The fires (to be\nconsecrated), and learning and practising the Veda. The Agnihotra sacrifice,\nand learning and practising the Veda. Guests (to be entertained), and learning\nand practising the Veda. Man's duty, and learning and practising the Veda.\nChildren, and learning and practising the Veda.\n\n(1-6) Marriage, and learning and practising the Veda. Children's children, and\nlearning and practising the Veda.\n\nSatyava _k_ as Rathitara thinks that the true only is necessary. Taponitya\nPaura _s_ ish _t_ i thinks that penance only is necessary. Naka Maudgalya\nthinks that learning and practising the Veda only are necessary,--for that is\npenance, that is penance.\n\n* * *\n\n### Footnotes\n\n[51:1](sbe15030.htm#fr_209) This chapter is meant to show that knowledge\nalone, though it secures the highest object, is not sufficient by itself, but\nmust be preceded by works. The learning of the Veda by heart and the\npractising of it so as not to forget it again, these two must always have been\npreviously performed.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 10](sbe15031.htm)\n\n"